title: H.S. girls gymnastics: Bergen County championships preview
text:
WHEN: Today, 5 p.m.; WHERE: Ridgewood 
TEAMS (in order of high score): Ramapo, Ridgewood, Pascack Regional, Holy Angels, Indian Hills 
RETURNING TOP 3: Emma Johnson, Ramapo (1st, all-around/vault/beam/floor; 2nd, bars); Samantha Marion, Ramapo (2nd, vault/beam; 3rd, AA/floor); Leah Gneco, Northern Highlands (3rd, vault); Amanda Katz, Ramapo (3rd, bars); Mika Tamura, Ridgewood (3rd, beam). 
TOP ALL-AROUNDS (season best): Johnson (38.4); Gneco (37.15); Katherine Muccio, Ridgewood (36.775); Victoria Purritano, Ridgewood (36.65); Katz (36.55); Kara Giacose, Ramapo (36.075); Shannon Furletti, Holy Angels (36.05). 
OUTLOOK: The top four teams are so strong, their scores could produce the highest combined total in the 37-year history of the meet. Still, Ramapo remains the cream of the crop and looks ready to capture a fifth straight title. 
— Greg Tartaglia © 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
